{
  // --- Why these two settings exist ---
  // The "Markdown Studio" extension (tanishq-chaudhary.its-markdown-studio)
  // opens *.md in a WYSIWYG custom editor and round-trips the file md → html → md
  // on save. That round-trip flattens inline links inside GFM table cells, which
  // strips the [name](projects/name.md) links in docs/plan.md's Projects Index
  // that docs/projects.index.test.ts requires. This has de-linked the index
  // repeatedly.

  // 1) Don't silently rewrite a file just because it was opened in the rich
  //    editor. With autoSave on (the extension default), merely opening a .md
  //    persists the lossy round-trip to disk. Off = opening is read-only until
  //    YOU explicitly save. (Note: if you edit AND save a link-in-table file in
  //    the rich editor, the round-trip still flattens those links — that's an
  //    upstream serializer bug; edit such files in the plain-text editor.)
  "markdownStudio.autoSave": false,

  // 2) Hard-protect the CI-critical index file: docs/plan.md always opens in the
  //    plain-text editor, never the WYSIWYG one. Other *.md still open in
  //    Markdown Studio by default. To force any file to text: right-click →
  //    "Reopen Editor With…" → "Text Editor".
  "workbench.editorAssociations": {
    "**/plan.md": "default"
  }
}
